xml.body:
@r169@
Item what booke it was that he receyvid of sir Thomas Moile, and
delyvered unto doctour London
Item what wourdes the chaunceller of Rochester said to hym, when he
said that hussay wolde helpe hym forwarde with his Articles
Item howe many tymes before passion weke, he resorted home, to
doctour Willoughbye, moving hym to put up suche Articles as
Serls he shoulde devise, and what answer doctour Willoughby made.
